{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Crossfades selected items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If any two items are adjacent then it creates a crossfade on the left side of the items' touch point\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If any two items are almost adjacent and their gap is less or equal to the default crossfade time then a crossfade is created\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If items overlap then it creates a crossfade at the overlapping area\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If there is a time selection covering part of both items, then it crossfades at the time selection area (items do not have to touch - closes the gap)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can be used with as many items in different tracks as you like\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Smart undo point creation (only if there has been at least one change)\par}
