{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If a note has notation information, REAPER stores this information as easily readable text inside a MIDI text event. For example, a note in channel 1 and pitch 64 that is notated in the high voice in the top staff will carry notation text "NOTE 0 64 staff 1 voice 1". (To figure out the code that REAPER uses, open the "Raw MIDI data" window, which will display all notation text.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script allows the user select notes based on notation text.\line It opens a dialog window in which the user can enter any text, such as "staff 1" "voice beam", and the script will select all notes with notation that matches the input.\line (To search for strings containing spaces, such as "voice 1", surround the string with quotation marks.)\par}
}

