{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Window for live use with 6 big customizable buttons showing region names, colors and progress bar\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Created for live use with backing tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Simple operation even with touch screen devices (like tablets running remote desktop of main computer)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 big clickable areas with any assignable Reaper actions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Showing region names and next region during playback\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Showing main window with color of current region and progress bar with color of next region (easy visual clues for song parts like chorus or bridge)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All elements are bright and super big, even on small mobile displays.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab User can change at the begining of the script following parameters: window starting size, font size, size of play/stop sign, height of progress bar, names and IDs of 6 actions.\sa180\par}
